722377f-a.text:
Park Avenue, east side, north from 94th Street, looking down
northern slope of Carnegie Hill.
O1d houses between 94th and 95th Streets contrast with new apartments in the block above.
No. 1225, on north east corner of 95th Street, was built in 1926, and
No. 1235 above it is just completed.
June 7, 1928.
P.L. Sperr,Photogrepher.

722384f-a.text:
Park Avenue, south from 97th Street, looking up Carnegie Hill
from above where the railroad emerges.
Squadron A Armory is seen on west side between 95th and 94th Streets,
on the site of the old 8th Regiment Armory.
October 11, 1927.
